textBeforeTable: TOP 50 NON-PREMIER COMICS Based on Total Unit Sales of Products Invoiced in November 2012 Other publishers in the top ten include Abstract Studios (Rachel Rising Volume 2: Fear No Malus ranked #7), Archie Comics (Sonic the Hedgehog Archives Volume 19 ranked #10), Dynamite Entertainment (The Boys Volume 12: The Bloody Doors Off ranked #2), Kodansha Comics (Sailor Moon ranked #6), Legendary Comics (The Tower Chronicles: Geisthawk Volume 2 ranked #5), Oni Press (Scott Pilgrim Color Edition Volume 2 ranked #3), and VIZ Media (three titles led by Naruto Volume 59, the month's top-selling manga title, at #4). KaBOOM!'s best-selling stories set in the Land of Ooo are collected in BOOM! Studios' Adventure Time Volume 1, the best-selling Non-Premier graphic novel for November. Other publishers in the top ten include Archie Comics, Avatar Press, Dynamite Entertainment, VIZ Media, and Yen Press. The Hive, the second volume in Charles Burns' Tintin-esque existential tale from Pantheon Books, was the best-selling Non-Premier Graphic Novel for October. Rounding out the top ten was BOOM! Studios with three titles in the top ten; Adventure Time #10 from their KaBOOM! all-ages imprint was their top book for November at #3. Valiant Entertainment had three titles in the top ten, led by Shadowman #1 at #2. In total, Dynamie had four titles in the top ten, including The Boys #72, the final issue of Garth Ennis and Darick Robertson's series, at #4; The Shadow #7 at #6; and The Shadow #8 at #9.
